{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}
{{Portal|Anglicanism}} [[Right Reverend|The Right Rev.]] ''' Cherakarottu Korula Jacob ''' was [[Anglican Bishop of Travancore and Cochin|Bishop of Travancore and Cochin]] in the mid twentieth century.<ref>[http://www.kerkrecht.nl/main.asp?pagetype=onderdeel&item=242&subitem=5941&page= Kerkrecht] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415021734/http://www.kerkrecht.nl/main.asp?pagetype=onderdeel&item=242&subitem=5941&page= |date=15 April 2012 }}</ref>

Jacob was educated at the [[University of Madras]] and [[ordained]] in 1915. He was a [[Church Mission Society|CMS]] [[priest]] at [[Melukavu]] until 1919. For the next twenty years he was [[Principal (academia)|Principal]] of the Cambridge Nicholson Institute at [[Kottayam]].<ref>[[Crockford's Clerical Directory]] Oxford, [[OUP]], 1948</ref> Later he was the [[Archdeacon]] of [[Mavelikkara]] before his elevation to the [[Episcopate]] in 1945.

