'''Diabolical rebaptism''' refers to the [[rebaptism]] of an individual in the name of the [[devil]]. It was a common accusation made against the accused at [[witch trials]], but seems to have been essentially the invention of [[demonology|demonologists]].<ref>''Eradicating the Devil's Minions: Anabaptists and Witches in Reformation Europe, 1535-1600'', Gary K. Waite, University of Toronto 2007, p. 100 - [https://books.google.com/books?id=Y0XbgWXKYAEC&pg=PA100&dq=%22Diabolical+rebaptism%22&hl=en&ei=f1Y_TK2bEZWd4QbB_Nz1Cg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCgQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q&f=false]</ref>
